### Send Notification

This endpoint allows you to send a notification to specific groups.

#### Request Body

- `userEmails` (array of strings, required is groups is empty): Specify the list of email to which the notification should be sent.

- `groups` (array of strings, required if userEmails is empty): Specify the groups to which the notification should be sent.

- `body` (string, required): The main content of the notification.

- `data` (object): Additional data to be included in the notification.

    - `screen` (string): Specify the screen to redirect to when the user clicks on the notification.

- `sound` (string): Specify the sound for the notification.

- `title` (string): The title of the notification.


#### Response

The response is in JSON format and follows the schema below:

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "failedTargets": {
            "type": ["null", "array"],
            "description": "List of targets that failed to receive the notification."
        },
        "success": {
            "type": "boolean",
            "description": "Indicates if the notification was successfully sent."
        },
        "totalTargets": {
            "type": "integer",
            "description": "Total number of targets to which the notification was sent."
        }
    }
}

 ```

### Upload Image

This endpoint allows users to upload an image.

#### Request

- Method: POST

- URL: `{{base_api_url}}/api/upload`

- Body:

    - `image` (file): The image file to be uploaded.


#### Response

The response is in JSON format and has the following schema:

``` json
{
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "success": {
            "type": "boolean"
        },
        "url": {
            "type": "string"
        }
    }
}

 ```

